From: Tony Luck <tony.luck@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Oct 2022 13:01:20 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm, hwpoison: when copy-on-write hits poison, take page
 offline
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.1.37
Git-commit: d302c2398ba269e788a4f37ae57c07a7fcabaa42

commit d302c2398ba269e788a4f37ae57c07a7fcabaa42 upstream.

Cannot call memory_failure() directly from the fault handler because
mmap_lock (and others) are held.

It is important, but not urgent, to mark the source page as h/w poisoned
and unmap it from other tasks.

Use memory_failure_queue() to request a call to memory_failure() for the
page with the error.

Also provide a stub version for CONFIG_MEMORY_FAILURE=n

Link: https://lkml.kernel.org/r/20221021200120.175753-3-tony.luck@intel.com
